  "prompt": "How many lokas (like heaven, hell, earth etc.) are there according to Hindu mythology?",
  "response": "According to Hindu mythology, there are traditionally 14 lokas (worlds or realms). These are broadly categorized into:\n\n1. **Seven higher lokas (heavens):**\n   - Satya-loka (Brahma-loka)\n   - Tapa-loka\n   - Jana-loka\n   - Mahar-loka\n   - Suvar-loka (Svarga-loka or Indra-loka)\n   - Bhuvar-loka (Pitri-loka)\n   - Bhur-loka (Earth)\n\n2. **Seven lower lokas (nether realms or hells):**\n   - Atala\n   - Vitala\n   - Sutala\n   - Talatala\n   - Mahatala\n   - Rasatala\n   - Patala\n\nThese realms are integral to the cosmology and metaphys\u0142sics described in ancient Hindu texts like the Puranas and the Vedas. Each loka presents a specific aspect of existence and consciousness, ranging from different levels of spiritual attainment to various degrees of material and cosmic reality.",
